        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 6 at 5:51PM CDT until July 6 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 550 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Nicodemus, or
10 miles east of Hill City, moving south at 25 mph. An additional
severe storm was located over Hill City and moving south.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Mesonet. The Hill City Airport gusted to 59 mph at 5:51pm
CT.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Hill City, Bogue, and Nicodemus.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
